sub_title: Officer at the Royal Netherlands Air Force
summary: Finishing my Ph.D. in Fungal genetics and biology, I am currently looking for positions in molecular biology and genetics. I have experience with analyzing genome variants using NGS, and I have combined this with using classical genetics to identify the genotypic background of mutant traits. Using our recently published CRISPR/Cas9 technique that I have set-up in our lab, I was able to reconstruct and analyze the impact of these SNPs on mutant phenotypes. Generally interested in DNA-work that involves functional characterization of mutant genes or altered gene regulation that results in aberrant phenotypes. I am an open, pro-active, enthusiastic and accurately working person with a result-oriented mindset.
